  "prompt": "What companies and startups use GitHub?",
  "response": "Many companies and startups across various industries use GitHub for version control, collaboration, and code sharing. Here are some notable examples:\n\n### Large Companies\n1. **Microsoft** - Acquired GitHub in 2018 and uses it extensively for many of its open-source projects and initiatives.\n2. **Google** - Uses GitHub for various open-source projects, including those related to Android and machine learning.\n3. **Facebook** - Hosts many of its open-source projects on GitHub, including React, React Native, and others.\n4. **IBM** - Leverages GitHub for its open-source contributions and projects, including cloud services and AI.\n5. **Netflix** - Uses GitHub for managing various open-source tools and projects related to cloud performance and microservices.\n\n### Startups\n1. **Slack** - Utilizes GitHub for its collaboration tools, including open-source projects for integrations and APIs.\n2. **Stripe** - Uses GitHub for open-source libraries and tools that interface with its payment platform.\n3. **Trello (Atlassian)** - While primarily a digital collaboration tool, Trello has open-source projects found on GitHub.\n4. **Twilio** - Hosts SDKs and libraries on GitHub for easier integration with their communications APIs.\n\n### Tech Companies\n1. **Spotify** - Uses GitHub for various open-source music-related projects and data processing tools.\n2. **Airbnb** - Maintains several open-source projects on GitHub, focusing on web development and design systems.\n3. **Docker** - The core technology behind containerization is developed and shared on GitHub.\n\n### Educational Institutions and Nonprofits\nMany universities and organizations maintain repositories on GitHub, sharing research and educational materials.\n\n### Other Notable Mentions\n- **Mozilla** - Hosts the Firefox browser and various projects on GitHub.\n- **Kubernetes** - Being an open-source container orchestration platform, much of its development occurs on GitHub.\n\nGitHub has become a go-to platform for coding collaboration and open-source projects, meaning that numerous companies leverage its capabilities for development, sharing code, and collaborating with the community.",
